Title: Milky Way Twilight Afterglow Grand Tetons
Body (HTML): This is a multiple exposure of the Grand Tetons with a pre-dawn glow, light painting, and the Milky Way above. A long exposure for the sky and stars, a second exposure with light painting, and a third exposure of the first light bathing the Moutain tops. All taken hours apart. Below you can see the snake river twisting through the scene. Some distant smoke and fog layers the hillside and mountain bases. The stars above glimmering over Mount Moran, Grand Teton, and the entire snow capped mountain range. Fall aspen trees littering the snake river in golden fall color leaves. Close by you could hear grizzly or brown bears rummaging about. You can see various constellations and star trails in the night sky.

Title: Colored Hills
Body (HTML): Painted Hills is named after the colorful layers of its hills corresponding to various geological eras, formed when the area was an ancient river floodplain. The black soil is lignite that was vegetative matter that grew along the floodplain. The grey coloring is mudstone, siltstone, and shale. The red coloring is laterite soil that formed by floodplain deposits when the area was warm and humid.Overlook Trail, Painted Hills, John Day Fossil Beds National Monument, Painted Hills Unit, Oregon, USA.
